      • UseCooIndices

        public void UseCooIndices(@Cast(value="int64_t*")
                          LongPointer indices_data,
                          @Cast(value="size_t")
                          long indices_num)
        Supplies COO format specific indices and marks the contained sparse tensor as being a COO format tensor. Values are supplied with a CreateSparseTensor() API. The supplied indices are not copied and the user allocated buffers lifespan must eclipse that of the OrtValue. The location of the indices is assumed to be the same as specified by OrtMemoryInfo argument at the creation time. pointer to the user allocated buffer with indices. Use nullptr for fully sparse tensors. number of indices entries. Use 0 for fully sparse tensors
